{{!-- Methodology --}}
<div class="page">
  {{> page-header title="Methodology"}}

  <h2>How We Audit</h2>
  <p class="summary-text" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
    Our audit uses a multi-layered approach combining automated crawling with manual analysis
    to provide a complete picture of your site's SEO health.
  </p>

  <div class="method-grid">
    <div class="method-card">
      <div class="method-num">1</div>
      <h4>Site Crawling</h4>
      <p>We crawl your site using a headless browser that renders JavaScript, following every internal
      link up to {{audit.maxPages}} pages. We respect robots.txt and rate-limit our requests.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="method-card">
      <div class="method-num">2</div>
      <h4>Lighthouse Analysis</h4>
      <p>We run Google Lighthouse on sampled pages to measure Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices,
      and SEO scores. Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS) are extracted from each run.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="method-card">
      <div class="method-num">3</div>
      <h4>On-Page SEO</h4>
      <p>Every page is analyzed for title tags, meta descriptions, heading structure, image optimization,
      canonical URLs, structured data, and social meta tags.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="method-card">
      <div class="method-num">4</div>
      <h4>Issue Detection</h4>
      <p>25 automated detectors identify critical, warning, and informational issues. Cross-page analysis
      catches duplicates, orphan pages, and redirect chains.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <h3>Confidence &amp; Limitations</h3>
  <div class="summary-text">
    <p>
      This audit represents a point-in-time snapshot. Scores may vary slightly between runs due to
      server response times and third-party resource loading. Lighthouse scores are measured in a
      simulated mobile environment on a mid-tier device with throttled CPU and network.
    </p>
    <p>
      The crawl covered <strong>{{formatNumber audit.pagesCrawled}}</strong> of an estimated
      {{formatNumber audit.maxPages}} discoverable pages. Pages behind authentication or generated
      dynamically based on user input are not included.
    </p>
  </div>

  {{> page-footer pageNum="3"}}
</div>
